[1 Chronicles 7:2](../../../bib/kjv/ch1007.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">ch1 7:2</span></span>

whose number: This was probably the number returned by Joab and his
assistants, when they made that census of the people with which God was
so much displeased. We find that the effective men of Issachar amounted
to 87,000 ([Ch1 7:5](../../../bib/kjv/ch1007.htm#005).md); 22,600 of whom
descended from Tola his eldest son; but whether the 36,000 ([Ch1
7:4](../../../bib/kjv/ch1007.htm#004).md) were descendants of Tola by Uzzi,
and the 22,600 his descendants by Tola's other sons; or whether another
of Issachar's sons be intended, does not clearly appear; though the
former seems the more obvious meaning. [Ch1
