<span class="margnote"><span id="an_023">ch1 7:23</span></span>

Beriah: that is, In evil

because: Many similar instances of the naming of children from passing
circumstances, occur throughout the sacred volume. See those of a
similar character with this verse: [Gen
35:18](../../../bib/kjv/gen035.htm#018.md), where Rachel, while dying,
names her new-born son Ben-oni, or, the son of my sorrow. So in [Sa1
4:21](../../../bib/kjv/sa1004.htm#021.md), the wife of Phinehas, on being
apprised of the death of Eli and her husband, and that the ark was taken
by the Philistines, while in the pains of travail, and dying, named her
son I-chabod, or, there is no glory. So also in [Ch1
9:4](../../../bib/kjv/ch1009.htm#004.md) of this book, we read that Jabez,
or, sorrowful, had that name given to him, because his mother "bare him
with sorrow." [Sa2 23:5](../../../bib/kjv/sa2023.htm#005.md)

